Canvas Assignment
Dashboard
Mac Menu Bar App
Version 1.0 — Draft
Date April 2026
Author Aarav Chhabra
Status In Review
Platform macOS 13+
A persistent Mac utility that surfaces Canvas LMS assignments and deadlines passively in the menu bar
— so you always know what's due the moment you open your laptop, without navigating to Canvas.
Canvas Assignment Dashboard Product Requirements Document
1. Problem & Motivation
Canvas's own interface is buried inside a browser tab — you have to actively seek it out to know what's due. This
creates a friction gap: assignments get missed not because you forgot about them, but because you never got a
timely, ambient reminder.
The goal is to make deadline awareness zero-effort. When you open your laptop, your assignment load should
already be visible — no clicking, no browser tab, no login.
Today (the problem) The solution
Canvas requires active navigation to see
what's due.
A persistent menu bar app that appears on wake.
Email notifications are easy to miss or ignore. Native macOS notifications with configurable lead times.
You carry the cognitive load of remembering
deadlines.
Ambient urgency dashboard — always there, never intrusive.
Submission status requires logging into
Canvas.
Submission badges pulled live from the Canvas API.
2. Target User
Primarily: UW students (or any Canvas LMS user) on macOS who manage multiple courses with staggered
deadlines and want ambient awareness without added friction.
User Profile
Attribute Detail
Platform Mac user, macOS 13 Ventura or later
Course load 3–6 active courses per quarter
Usage pattern Heavy multitasker; switches between apps frequently
Pain point Misses or nearly misses assignments occasionally
Preference Prefers quick glance over deep UI navigation
Canvas usage Logs into Canvas daily but finds it cumbersome
Jobs To Be Done
