3. Core Features
Features are prioritized P0 (must-have for launch), P1 (important), and P2 (nice-to-have). P0 features block the
MVP; P1 and P2 ship in subsequent phases.
F1 Persistent always-on dashboard P0
A floating menu bar app that appears on wake, showing upcoming assignments. Pinned to the macOS menu bar — never
needs to be manually launched after initial setup. Survives reboots via a Login Item registration.
F2 Canvas live sync P0
Pulls assignments, quizzes, and discussions from Canvas via the REST API or iCal feed. Auto-refreshes on a configurable
interval (default 30 min), on wake, and on demand. Displays course name, assignment title, due date/time, and submission
status.
F3 Urgency timeline view P0
Assignments displayed in time-bucketed rows: Overdue, Due Today, Due Tomorrow, This Week, Coming Up. Color coding
by urgency (red / amber / green) and by course. Overdue items float to the top with a distinct visual treatment.
F4 One-click Canvas link P1
Clicking any assignment opens its Canvas page directly in the default browser. No copy-pasting, no searching Canvas
manually.
F5 macOS notifications P1
System notification at configurable intervals before a deadline (e.g. 24 h, 2 h, 30 min). Respects macOS Focus modes.
Notification action button opens Canvas directly.
F6 Personal task layer P2
Optional manual tasks added alongside Canvas items — e.g. 'Start essay outline'. Displayed with a visual distinction from
synced items. Stored locally only; not synced anywhere.
F7 Course filter & settings P2
Toggle visibility per course. Set per-course colors. Configure lookahead window (1 week / 2 weeks / full quarter). Option to
hide completed or graded assignments.
