4. Canvas API Integration
UW Canvas exposes a documented REST API and iCal calendar feed. Two integration approaches are
available, suitable for different development phases.
Approach Details
Option A — REST API (recommended
for v1.1+)
Uses a Personal Access Token generated in Canvas Settings. Richer data:
submission status, point values, file attachments. Token stored securely in
macOS Keychain.
Option B — iCal feed (recommended for
MVP)
Canvas exposes a calendar .ics feed. No token needed, just a URL. Limited to
due date + title. Fast to integrate — ideal for getting the MVP working quickly.
Key REST API Endpoints
Endpoint Used for
GET /api/v1/courses Fetch active courses and their metadata
GET /api/v1/planner/items Unified assignment, quiz, discussion feed
GET
/api/v1/courses/:id/assignments
Per-course assignment detail (fallback)
GET /api/v1/users/self/upcomin
g_events
Upcoming calendar events
Authentication
Personal Access Token (PAT) generated once by the user inside Canvas (Account > Settings > Approved
Integrations > New Access Token). Stored in macOS Keychain via the keytar library. Never written to disk in
plaintext. All API requests include an Authorization: Bearer <token> header.
Rate Limiting & Error Handling
Scenario Handling
HTTP 401 / 403 Clear stored token; show re-auth prompt in settings panel
HTTP 429 (rate limited) Exponential backoff: 60 s, 120 s, 240 s; show warning badge
Network offline Skip sync cycle; show 'Offline — cached data' footer with last-sync time
iCal parse error Log malformed event, skip it, continue parsing the rest of the feed
