6. Build Options
Three realistic implementation paths, ordered by recommended suitability:
Option Pros Cons
A — Electron + React
(recommended)
Build with web tech. Fast iteration if you
know JavaScript/TypeScript. Rich
ecosystem.
~150 MB binary (Chromium bundled).
Slightly heavier feel than pure native.
B — Swift / SwiftUI (native Mac
app)
Best performance and native feel. Direct
macOS API access. Tiny binary (~5 MB).
Steeper learning curve. Slower to build if
not experienced with Swift.
C — Raycast extension
(no-code MVP)
Quickest to get running. Zero setup
friction. No coding required.
Not truly always-on. Limited
customization. Requires Raycast to be
installed.
Recommended Start with Option A (Electron + React) for the MVP. Use the Canvas iCal feed first to
avoid auth complexity. Add the REST API in v1.1 once the UI is solid. Rewrite
performance-critical parts in Swift later if needed.
